                        "text": "\ud83c\uddef\ud83c\uddf5 Comment TOKYO and I\u2019ll send you a free Tokyo Travel Guide + 5 day itinerary including how to get there, where to stay, what to do and how to buy tickets.\n\nGet 10% off Japan train tickets and activities on Klook by using code MINYWANDER (10% for new users and over $50 spend, 3% for existing users).\n\n\ud83c\uddef\ud83c\uddf5 10 things to do in Tokyo \u2b07\ufe0f\n\nThere\u2019s no city quite like Tokyo. From towering skyscrapers to bustling markets, serene temples to glitzy neon signs, there is something for everyone.\n\n\ud83c\udf24\ufe0f Shibuya Sky - observation deck located by Shibuya Scramble Crossing. \n\ud83d\udcab TeamLab Planets or Borderless - interactive digital art museums with galleries of immersive installations.\n\ud83d\udeb6\u200d\u2640\ufe0f Shibuya Scramble Crossing - fun place to people-watch as it is the largest pedestrian crossing. Located in front of Shibuya Station - estimated 1000-2500 people crossing at once.\n\ud83d\uddfc Tokyo Tower - symbol of Japan\u2019s economic growth. Used to be the tallest building in Tokyo until Tokyo Skytree was built in 2012.\n\ud83d\udc1f Tsukiji Outer Market - market containing seafood, vegetables, traditional food materials. It is touristy and expensive, but worth checking out at least once.\n\ud83d\uddfb Mt. Fuji Day Trip - take the train to Lake Kawaguchiko for sights of Mt. Fuji. Take caution as Mt. Fuji is only visible on clear days!\n\ud83c\udfee Senso-ji Temple - in the historic Asakusa district, this is Tokyo\u2019s oldest temple. \n\u26e9\ufe0f Meiji Jingu Shrine - this shrine is a peaceful retreat in a forested area with colorful display of kazaridaru or sake barrels. \n\ud83d\udecd\ufe0f Harajuku - trendy district with Takeshita Street at its heart, lined with vibrant fashion stores, colorful boutiques, quirky shops, and cafes (and crepe stores). \n\ud83c\udf63 Sushi Omakase - chef curated course meal made fresh in front of you, where every bite is a masterpiece. \n\n\ud83d\udccc Save this post for your Tokyo trip!\n\ud83d\udc49\ud83c\udffb Follow\u00a0@minywander\u00a0for more travel inspo and tips!\n\n#tokyo\u00a0#tokyojapan\u00a0#japan\u00a0#explorejapan\u00a0#visittokyo\u00a0#visitjapan\n\nTokyo things to do | Best activities in Tokyo | must see in Tokyo | what to do in tokyo | tokyo top sights | tokyo bucketlist"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
